habitat_description: The range of sierra treefrog expands from central California, western Utah, Nevada, Idaho, eastern Oregon, and northwestern Montana; to a lesser extent into eastern Washington and British Columbia (Green et al. 2014). In California, this species is found in the Sierra Nevada from sea level through the mountainous zone into the high elevation lakes (approx. 3660) (Green et al. 2014). Habitat of preference includes exclusive areas from salmonids, various grasslands, old fields, agricultural parcels, and forests (Green et al. 2014). According to californiaherps.com, it is unclear where the southern overlapping zone with P. hypochondriaca lies, and where the northern boundary with P. regilla is comprised.
